    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Remix; Turning Tables | Hangar-7</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Gisela Williams</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Williams, Gisela</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Ikarus, restaurant in Salzburg, Austria, rotates famous guest chefs for month at a time; photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>It's a restaurant concept that only someone wired on a high-caffeine energy drink could conceive: each month, a famous guest chef creates the menu. It's fitting, then, that the proprietor of this place, Ikarus, is Dietrich Mateschitz, the Austrian owner of Red Bull. The restaurant has glass walls overlooking the antique planes in Red Bull's Hangar-7, near the airport in Salzburg, Austria. Past chefs include Gray Kunz, Xavier Pellicer (of Abac in Barcelona) and Christian Delouvrier. Go to www.hangar-7.com.</p>
        <p>GISELA WILLIAMS</p>
      </block>
